7
00:01:15,607 --> 00:01:17,359
He's late today.

8
00:01:18,567 --> 00:01:20,205
[CAMERA CLICKS]

9
00:01:24,887 --> 00:01:26,479
MAN 1: Where are you?
Are you right there?

10
00:01:26,647 --> 00:01:28,126
MAN 2:
No, I'm across the street.

11
00:01:30,047 --> 00:01:31,366
[CAMERA CLICKING]

12
00:01:35,567 --> 00:01:36,602
MAN 1:
Get closer than that.

13
00:01:36,767 --> 00:01:39,600
MAN 2 [OVER RADIO]: I'm not gonna
lose him. I'm not gonna lose him.

14
00:01:39,767 --> 00:01:41,405
MAN 1:
Pay attention, guys.

15
00:01:46,327 --> 00:01:50,286
9:01, down Granville Park. Again.

16
00:01:53,047 --> 00:01:55,197
Okay, switch to channel seven.

17
00:01:55,647 --> 00:01:56,875
[CAMERA CLICKS]

18
00:02:02,367 --> 00:02:04,801
[CAMERA CLICKING]

19
00:02:05,687 --> 00:02:07,484
WOMAN:
Sarah!

20
00:02:08,767 --> 00:02:09,961
Hi.

21
00:02:21,527 --> 00:02:23,358
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

22
00:02:23,607 --> 00:02:25,757
[CAMERA CLICKS]

23
00:02:30,807 --> 00:02:32,559
MAN 1:
Control the flow of traffic.

24
00:02:34,327 --> 00:02:36,636
BO Y:
Come on! Come here, Rusty!

25
00:02:43,567 --> 00:02:45,842
WOMAN:
Rusty. Rusty, come here.

26
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,285
Come... Rusty!

27
00:02:48,887 --> 00:02:50,445
Come on, boy.

28
00:02:51,007 --> 00:02:52,645
MAN 1:
Come on. We're gonna be late.

29
00:02:52,807 --> 00:02:54,365
MAN 2:
Hello, Jack.

30
00:02:54,527 --> 00:02:56,006
[CAMERA CLICKS]

31
00:02:56,727 --> 00:02:59,560
BETH: Sarah, could you turn it down?
SARAH: What?

32
00:02:59,727 --> 00:03:02,480
BETH: The music, if that's what it is.
Turn it down.

33
00:03:02,647 --> 00:03:04,603
SARAH: Why?
BETH: Has anyone let the dog out yet?

34
00:03:04,967 --> 00:03:08,437
AND Y: It's Sarah's turn! I did it last time!
BETH: It takes, what, two seconds?

35
00:03:08,607 --> 00:03:10,563
AND Y:
Rusty, no! Leave it alone!

36
00:03:10,727 --> 00:03:12,285
Come on!

37
00:03:13,447 --> 00:03:14,960
SARAH:
Andy, stop it.

38
00:03:15,127 --> 00:03:19,279
Andy! Mom, tell Andy to get that thing
out of here. It's screwing up the TV.

39
00:03:19,767 --> 00:03:21,246
AND Y:
Idiot.

40
00:03:21,407 --> 00:03:23,921
Andy, a little help here, okay?

41
00:03:24,087 --> 00:03:26,123
SARAH: Moron.
- Idiot moron.

42
00:03:26,287 --> 00:03:28,437
- Moron idiot.
- Nobody's an idiot.

43
00:03:28,607 --> 00:03:30,643
AND Y: Except for her.
- Nobody's a moron.

44
00:03:30,807 --> 00:03:33,765
AND Y: Except for her.
SARAH: Andy, stop it!

45
00:03:33,927 --> 00:03:36,077
I'm trying to watch this.

46
00:03:36,247 --> 00:03:38,203
Those two home together all week?

47
00:03:38,367 --> 00:03:41,837
- There's no school till Monday.
- Oh, boy. What's your day like?

48
00:03:42,007 --> 00:03:45,397
Finish the details on the Morgan house.
They're pouring the footings today.

49
00:03:45,807 --> 00:03:49,243
Then I have to find a guitar teacher
for Sarah, pay some bills...

50
00:03:49,407 --> 00:03:50,726
...and schlepping the kids.

51
00:03:50,887 --> 00:03:54,482
You should get yourself a hobby,
keep yourself busy.

52
00:03:54,647 --> 00:03:56,717
- I already have a hobby.
- Yeah?

53
00:03:56,887 --> 00:03:59,401
And it's taking care of you.

54
00:03:59,567 --> 00:04:01,444
I don't deserve you.

55
00:04:01,607 --> 00:04:02,801
No, you don't.

56
00:04:02,967 --> 00:04:05,686
We owe Arlin and Vee a dinner.
Wanna do it this week?

57
00:04:05,847 --> 00:04:08,884
Well, they're home this week.
I just wanna be with the kids.

58
00:04:09,047 --> 00:04:10,162
SARAH: Mom!
- Really?

59
00:04:10,327 --> 00:04:12,363
SARAH:
Tell Andy to get that thing out of here!

60
00:04:13,887 --> 00:04:16,606
You should have Marci drop
my blue suit off at the cleaners.

61
00:04:16,767 --> 00:04:18,758
BETH:
Marci's in Manila till the 26th.

62
00:04:18,927 --> 00:04:21,646
Here, sport, give me this for a second.

63
00:04:22,167 --> 00:04:25,682
- Mom! Excuse me, does anybody care?
- This is what's doing it.

64
00:04:25,847 --> 00:04:28,566
Put this in my office.
I'll show you how we can fix it.

65
00:04:28,727 --> 00:04:31,799
Okay? And, yes, I do care.

66
00:04:33,367 --> 00:04:36,086
- Goodbye.
- Bye, Jack.

67
00:04:36,247 --> 00:04:38,283
AND Y: Bye, Dad.
JACK: Bye, Andy.

68
00:04:39,407 --> 00:04:41,398
Don't torture your sister.

69
00:04:41,567 --> 00:04:46,277
Sarah, this dog needs to go out.
Don't forget his new collar.

70
00:04:46,447 --> 00:04:49,007
- Sarah.
- Bye, Jack.

71
00:04:54,447 --> 00:04:56,517
MAN [OVER RADIO]:
- Getting a break in the weather...

72
00:04:56,687 --> 00:04:58,359
...before getting hit
by a couple of storms.

73
00:04:58,527 --> 00:05:00,483
That'll make the drive more difficult.

74
00:05:00,647 --> 00:05:03,957
Looks like smooth sailing this morning
heading into downtown Seattle.

75
00:05:04,127 --> 00:05:08,643
We've been seeing slowdowns and heavy
traffic just about everywhere else...

76
00:05:32,567 --> 00:05:34,797
- Morning.
- Morning, Richard.

77
00:05:34,967 --> 00:05:38,323
- Morning, Cindy. How are you?
- Morning, Jack. Great, thanks.

78
00:05:38,927 --> 00:05:40,485
How do I say this, Bobby?

79
00:05:40,647 --> 00:05:43,878
- Um, no.
- Come on, Janet. I don't see why not.

80
00:05:44,047 --> 00:05:47,119
Look, Bobby, here's how this works.
You ask me out, which you did.

81
00:05:47,287 --> 00:05:48,720
I say no, which I did.

82
00:05:48,887 --> 00:05:52,047
You say, "Okay," and ask somebody
else. You don't keep asking me.

83
00:05:52,047 --> 00:05:54,117
At what point does it become
sexual harassment?

84
00:05:54,287 --> 00:05:55,481
Right about now, Bobby.

85
00:05:55,647 --> 00:05:57,478
- Mr. Stanfield.
- Morning, boss.

86
00:05:58,167 --> 00:06:00,556
- Kid's persistent.
- I don't know why.

87
00:06:00,727 --> 00:06:03,287
- The usual reason, I suppose.
- Have you seen Ravi yet?

88
00:06:03,447 --> 00:06:05,165
No, I'm on my way now, though.

89
00:06:05,327 --> 00:06:06,806
Don't forget, merger meeting.

90
00:06:08,487 --> 00:06:10,796
- Nice flowers.
- Born-again Bobby.

91
00:06:10,967 --> 00:06:14,482
- Maybe he's trying to save your soul.
- He'd need bigger blossoms than that.

92
00:06:25,487 --> 00:06:27,000
- Good morning, Betty.
- Morning.

93
00:06:27,167 --> 00:06:29,601
- How we doing?
- Pike Street system's running slow.

94
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:32,440
I'll tell Carol when she gets in.
We'll get after it.

95
00:06:32,607 --> 00:06:35,644
Merger goes through, we'll go in
and replace the whole thing.

96
00:06:35,807 --> 00:06:37,206
Yeah.

97
00:06:38,487 --> 00:06:41,001
- Morning, sir.
- Good morning, Rick.

98
00:06:42,607 --> 00:06:44,245
Hey, Ravi. What have we got?

99
00:06:45,527 --> 00:06:47,677
Brute-force login.
The interesting thing is...

100
00:06:47,847 --> 00:06:50,441
...he's coming in through Hong Kong,
Korea and Malaysia...

101
00:06:50,607 --> 00:06:53,679
...but he's trying sequential account
numbers. He's hacking all over.

102
00:06:53,847 --> 00:06:55,439
Move over for me.

103
00:06:57,447 --> 00:07:01,042
JACK: Let's try a rule change on him,
see what he does.

104
00:07:01,207 --> 00:07:04,563
Put in an IPS signature
that black-holes the pattern.

105
00:07:05,647 --> 00:07:09,037
- See if that slows him down.
- That'd slow me down.

106
00:07:09,207 --> 00:07:12,404
- That'd be resistant to false positives.
- Yep.

107
00:07:12,567 --> 00:07:14,478
- Thanks.
- Huh.

108
00:07:15,607 --> 00:07:18,963
MAN 1: Loss is higher than one would
expect, considering your level of security.

109
00:07:19,127 --> 00:07:20,526
Just write it off?

110
00:07:20,687 --> 00:07:22,643
MAN 2: That depends on how
you view the statistics.

111
00:07:22,807 --> 00:07:25,958
They're not particularly high,
given the fact that...

112
00:07:26,127 --> 00:07:30,325
...we're pushing the business into
some new and uncharted areas.

113
00:07:30,487 --> 00:07:32,842
Online banking is where
the business is heading.

114
00:07:33,007 --> 00:07:34,281
Where we have our branches...

115
00:07:34,447 --> 00:07:37,837
...we'll provide our customers with
more ways to control their money.

116
00:07:38,007 --> 00:07:40,123
As you can see by the chart,
after the merger...

117
00:07:40,287 --> 00:07:42,881
...Accuwest will have 1100 branches
in 13 states...

118
00:07:43,047 --> 00:07:46,323
...with over 100 billion in assets.
So to answer you, Harry, yes...

119
00:07:46,487 --> 00:07:51,242
...we do see a reasonable level
of fraud loss as a cost of doing business.

120
00:07:51,407 --> 00:07:54,001
- How many branches do you have?
- Twenty-seven.

121
00:07:54,887 --> 00:07:56,479
As head of network security, Jack...

122
00:07:56,647 --> 00:07:59,844
...you've never really had to think
in terms of economies of scale.

123
00:08:00,007 --> 00:08:03,966
- But your philosophy of risk is...
JACK: Wait a second, Gary.

124
00:08:04,127 --> 00:08:08,439
Make this clear for me, will you?
What exactly is my philosophy of risk?

125
00:08:08,607 --> 00:08:11,644
- No need to take this personally.
- I take it personally, goddamn it.

126
00:08:11,807 --> 00:08:15,117
I've spent 20 years protecting this bank,
its customers and shareholders...

127
00:08:15,287 --> 00:08:16,720
...from unnecessary risk.

128
00:08:17,767 --> 00:08:19,997
Jack, I don't think you're hearing
what I'm saying.

129
00:08:20,167 --> 00:08:22,681
JACK: I hear what you're saying.
Fraud loss is inevitable...

130
00:08:22,847 --> 00:08:26,157
...pass it on to the customers
as the cost of doing business.

131
00:08:26,327 --> 00:08:27,919
JACK:
We don't wanna do that, do we?

132
00:08:30,087 --> 00:08:32,885
ARLIN: We're all here to serve
the customers. Let's try and get along.

133
00:08:33,047 --> 00:08:36,562
- We can have the best of both worlds.
- Doesn't exist, Arlin.

134
00:08:37,847 --> 00:08:40,725
JACK: Look, I'm sorry. This went on
a little longer than I anticipated.

135
00:08:40,967 --> 00:08:43,606
There's stuff I really have to get to.

136
00:08:45,847 --> 00:08:48,884
- Okay, let's get on with it.
GARY: Network attacks...

137
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:50,961
...network activity.

138
00:08:54,567 --> 00:08:56,558
- Where is this guy?
- He's in reception.

139
00:08:56,727 --> 00:08:58,922
He said it's personal.
Should I get him?

140
00:08:59,087 --> 00:09:00,884
No, I'll walk over there.

141
00:09:05,087 --> 00:09:07,396
Mr. Stanfield, Mr. Hughes.

142
00:09:09,727 --> 00:09:11,285
Jack Stanfield, Mr. Hughes.

143
00:09:11,447 --> 00:09:13,039
- Do I know you?
- I know you.

144
00:09:13,847 --> 00:09:15,963
- Do you have a card?
- Oh, yeah.

145
00:09:18,767 --> 00:09:21,201
DHD Financial. What can I do for you?

146
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:23,119
You can give me
the $95,000 you owe me.

147
00:09:23,767 --> 00:09:25,837
- I don't know what you're talking about.
- No?

148
00:09:26,007 --> 00:09:28,680
I'm collecting for GambleNet U.S.A.
Does that ring a bell?

149
00:09:28,847 --> 00:09:32,396
- No, it doesn't.
- You racked up 95,000 in online wagers.

150
00:09:32,567 --> 00:09:34,922
And I got the paperwork to prove it.

151
00:09:35,087 --> 00:09:37,362
You got the wrong Jack Stanfield.
I don't gamble.

152
00:09:37,527 --> 00:09:41,156
- I don't have any debt. Check your facts.
- You're a deadbeat. See you in court.

153
00:09:41,327 --> 00:09:43,921
- Laurie, call security.
- Don't bother, sweetheart.

154
00:09:44,087 --> 00:09:48,205
Gambling's an addiction, Mr. Stanfield.
Get some help.

155
00:10:06,007 --> 00:10:08,840
JANET: Well, I thought the idea
was to match it to the curtains.

156
00:10:09,007 --> 00:10:11,521
- Yes, but if you do that...
- Nice flowers.

157
00:10:11,687 --> 00:10:12,961
Bobby?

158
00:10:13,127 --> 00:10:15,687
That would be the wrong thing to do,
don't you think?

159
00:10:16,527 --> 00:10:19,599
HARRY: What's up, partner?
- Take a look at this.

160
00:10:22,407 --> 00:10:24,557
Wow. Who were you betting on?

161
00:10:24,727 --> 00:10:26,319
I wasn't betting. I don't gamble.

162
00:10:26,487 --> 00:10:29,126
- I don't even know how.
- Well, that's obvious.

163
00:10:29,287 --> 00:10:32,757
Think somebody got my information off
the bank's internal network or what?

164
00:10:32,927 --> 00:10:34,804
Are you doubting yourself
in your old age?

165
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:37,481
No. More likely a dumpster diver...

166
00:10:37,647 --> 00:10:40,115
...somebody sifting through your trash.
- Maybe.

167
00:10:41,167 --> 00:10:43,886
A debt collector showed up
this morning about it.

168
00:10:44,047 --> 00:10:45,685
Don't worry. I'll clean it up.

169
00:10:45,847 --> 00:10:48,236
It's just a pain in the ass.

170
00:10:48,407 --> 00:10:50,159
Bill Cox? Guy from Atlanta.

171
00:10:50,327 --> 00:10:52,204
- Supposed to have a drink.
- I can do 5:30.

172
00:10:52,367 --> 00:10:54,039
I wanna get home early, pizza night.

173
00:10:54,207 --> 00:10:56,323
- Good. I'll let him know.
- Okay.

174
00:10:59,287 --> 00:11:00,515
[PHONE RINGS]

175
00:11:01,607 --> 00:11:03,199
- Hey, you.
JACK [OVER PHONE]: Hi, hon.

176
00:11:03,367 --> 00:11:06,484
Harry and I need to see a guy
for a few minutes after work.

177
00:11:06,647 --> 00:11:08,603
- Okay if I'm late?
- What are you thinking?

178
00:11:08,767 --> 00:11:11,440
I don 't know, 45 minutes, tops.

179
00:11:11,607 --> 00:11:13,757
We'll see you when we see you.
Love you.

180
00:11:13,927 --> 00:11:16,043
Love you too. Bye.

181
00:11:20,927 --> 00:11:23,521
I see him. My question is this:

182
00:11:23,687 --> 00:11:27,441
Do we really wanna work
for those Accuwest morons?

183
00:11:27,607 --> 00:11:30,767
- I'll listen to what he has to say.
HARRY: This guy could be our future.

184
00:11:30,767 --> 00:11:32,723
JACK:
Okay, okay.

185
00:11:32,887 --> 00:11:34,843
HARRY: Bill.
- Good to see you, Harry.

186
00:11:35,287 --> 00:11:37,517
- Bill Cox, Jack Stanfield.
- How are you?

187
00:11:37,687 --> 00:11:40,247
I've been looking forward
to meeting you. Please, sit.

188
00:11:40,407 --> 00:11:41,760
Thank you.

189
00:11:47,087 --> 00:11:48,440
[DOORBELL RINGS]

190
00:11:48,727 --> 00:11:52,845
Sarah, the pizza's here.
My wallet's by the door.

191
00:11:56,367 --> 00:11:57,595
[DOORBELL RINGS]

192
00:11:57,807 --> 00:12:00,116
Is somebody gonna get that?

193
00:12:02,447 --> 00:12:04,483
WAITRESS: Here you go.
BILL: So listen...

194
00:12:04,687 --> 00:12:07,847
...I don't know how much
Harry's told you about what I do.

195
00:12:07,847 --> 00:12:11,044
Not a lot. Just that you're in banking.

196
00:12:11,207 --> 00:12:14,005
I have a company that provides
banking-support services...

197
00:12:14,167 --> 00:12:17,364
...mainly in the South, but, really,
I'm an old-fashioned entrepreneur.

198
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:19,525
[YELLING OVER TV]

199
00:12:20,127 --> 00:12:24,120
If that's a scary movie, turn it off.
Your brother won't sleep for a week.

200
00:12:26,167 --> 00:12:28,317
BETH: I'm so sorry to make you...
- Hello.

201
00:12:28,807 --> 00:12:29,876
Aah!

202
00:12:31,647 --> 00:12:33,524
BETH: Sarah!
- Mom.

203
00:12:33,687 --> 00:12:34,756
Call 911!

204
00:12:34,927 --> 00:12:38,397
There's over 200 regional banks
in the U.S. Alone that have nothing...

205
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:42,003
...like the sophistication of the system
you developed for Landrock.

206
00:12:42,247 --> 00:12:43,646
[SCREAMING]

207
00:12:43,807 --> 00:12:45,240
BETH:
Sarah! Leave her alone!

208
00:12:46,487 --> 00:12:48,557
With your system's software...

209
00:12:48,727 --> 00:12:51,764
...Harry's expertise in law enforcement
and the physical security...

210
00:12:51,927 --> 00:12:53,360
...you're an unbeatable team.

211
00:12:54,007 --> 00:12:55,725
PIM:
Hey! Come here!

212
00:12:55,887 --> 00:12:57,036
No!

213
00:12:57,207 --> 00:12:59,926
- What are you doing to me? Get away!
PIM: Shut up!

214
00:13:00,087 --> 00:13:01,645
You'd be your own bosses.

215
00:13:01,807 --> 00:13:03,877
I'd just supply the money.

216
00:13:05,087 --> 00:13:07,282
BETH: Don't hurt my children.
- Shut up!

217
00:13:07,447 --> 00:13:09,597
Oh, my God, what do you want?

218
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:12,076
I have to think about
a couple of other options...

219
00:13:12,247 --> 00:13:14,317
...but this sounds very attractive.

220
00:13:14,487 --> 00:13:15,681
Okay, good.

221
00:13:16,247 --> 00:13:17,919
[SCREAMING]

222
00:13:18,167 --> 00:13:19,441
I hate to break this up.

223
00:13:19,607 --> 00:13:21,199
JACK: I gotta get home.
- Family man.

224
00:13:21,367 --> 00:13:24,086
No! Daddy!

225
00:13:26,007 --> 00:13:27,599
So how many kids do you have?

226
00:13:27,767 --> 00:13:30,918
- Two. Boy, 8. Girl, 14.
- Wow.

227
00:13:31,087 --> 00:13:33,760
- Sure you don't need a ride?
- No, thanks, Harry. I'm fine.

228
00:13:33,927 --> 00:13:35,121
Going back tonight?

229
00:13:35,287 --> 00:13:40,725
- No, I've got some business in town.
- Well, great meeting you. Take care.

230
00:13:55,287 --> 00:13:57,243
She has beautiful eyes,
your daughter.

231
00:13:57,967 --> 00:13:59,480
What?

232
00:14:00,887 --> 00:14:03,162
Jesus, what...?

233
00:14:03,847 --> 00:14:05,360
Oh, my God. What do you want?

234
00:14:05,847 --> 00:14:08,281
I wanna get you home.
It's pizza night.

235
00:14:10,407 --> 00:14:11,806
Drive.

236
00:14:12,887 --> 00:14:14,036
Drive.

237
00:14:30,847 --> 00:14:33,680
Liam, we're on our way.
Everything all right?

238
00:14:33,847 --> 00:14:37,681
Fine, the house is secure.
And we're setting up now.

239
00:14:37,847 --> 00:14:40,122
I wanna talk to my wife.

240
00:14:40,287 --> 00:14:42,517
You hear that, Liam?
He wants to talk to his wife.

241
00:14:42,687 --> 00:14:44,564
They can't talk right now.

242
00:14:46,047 --> 00:14:47,241
She's busy.

243
00:15:20,727 --> 00:15:22,206
JACK:
Who are you?

244
00:15:22,367 --> 00:15:24,085
What's this about?

245
00:15:26,687 --> 00:15:28,723
What do you want from me?

246
00:15:48,207 --> 00:15:49,845
This is your exit, Jack.

247
00:16:23,247 --> 00:16:26,000
MAN [OVER TV]: Three defenders had
the chance to put him on the ground.

248
00:16:26,167 --> 00:16:27,236
VEL:
They're here.

249
00:16:27,407 --> 00:16:30,797
MAN [OVER TV]: As good as he's
been. Tremendous effort to stay alive.

250
00:16:47,807 --> 00:16:50,037
- Where are they?
- Through here.

251
00:16:56,727 --> 00:16:58,479
Jesus.

252
00:16:58,647 --> 00:17:00,717
JACK: What is this?
AND Y: Daddy.

253
00:17:00,887 --> 00:17:03,242
Why have you done this,
for God's sake?

254
00:17:04,087 --> 00:17:06,203
It's okay. They're children!

255
00:17:07,207 --> 00:17:09,516
I said, "If they were trouble."
Were they trouble?

256
00:17:09,687 --> 00:17:12,918
- They were noisy.
- Yes, we made an executive decision.

257
00:17:13,087 --> 00:17:15,282
But you're a criminal, Willy,
not an executive.

258
00:17:15,447 --> 00:17:17,039
- But I thought you said...
- Shut up.

259
00:17:17,207 --> 00:17:19,596
AND Y: Daddy.
- I wanna know what you want...

260
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:20,995
...and I wanna know now.

261
00:17:22,007 --> 00:17:23,201
Beth...

262
00:17:23,367 --> 00:17:26,484
...I'm sorry about all of this.
I am, but, well...

263
00:17:28,327 --> 00:17:29,476
There we are.

264
00:17:29,647 --> 00:17:33,765
Uh, I need you to talk to your husband.
He listens to you.

265
00:17:34,647 --> 00:17:38,003
I need you to make him understand that
if he doesn't do exactly as I ask...

266
00:17:38,167 --> 00:17:40,886
...I will kill you and your two children.

267
00:17:41,687 --> 00:17:44,406
But if you can make him listen, Beth...

268
00:17:45,047 --> 00:17:47,242
...if you can make him do
what I want...

269
00:17:47,407 --> 00:17:50,479
...you'll all walk away from
this unpleasantness unscathed.

270
00:17:50,927 --> 00:17:52,201
COX:
Not because I'm a nice man...

271
00:17:53,327 --> 00:17:57,036
...simply because there'll be no reason
for me to hurt you.

272
00:18:00,407 --> 00:18:01,556
Make sense?

273
00:18:04,727 --> 00:18:06,957
Can I rely on your cooperation?

274
00:18:07,447 --> 00:18:09,836
- Just tell him yes.
- Yes.

275
00:18:10,927 --> 00:18:12,201
Sarah?

276
00:18:12,807 --> 00:18:14,479
Fine.

277
00:18:15,887 --> 00:18:17,684
And you, big fella?

278
00:18:18,087 --> 00:18:19,645
Maybe.

279
00:18:19,927 --> 00:18:22,964
BETH: Andy.
- No, it's all right. It's honest.

280
00:18:25,287 --> 00:18:27,721
Do you keep a gun
in the house, Jack?

281
00:18:28,887 --> 00:18:30,525
No.

282
00:18:32,527 --> 00:18:34,165
- Daddy!
- I'm okay.

283
00:18:34,367 --> 00:18:35,686
BETH: It's okay.
JACK: Don't worry.

284
00:18:35,847 --> 00:18:37,724
- It's okay.
- I'm all right. I'm okay.

285
00:18:37,887 --> 00:18:39,081
Pass me the gun.

286
00:18:40,007 --> 00:18:41,360
COX:
It's empty.

287
00:18:45,167 --> 00:18:47,123
You lied to me, Jack.

288
00:18:48,647 --> 00:18:50,638
COX:
Don't let it happen again.

289
00:18:52,567 --> 00:18:54,637
You have an excellent alarm system.

290
00:18:54,807 --> 00:18:56,877
What are alarms for, Andy?

291
00:18:57,687 --> 00:19:00,406
- To keep people out.
COX: That's right.

292
00:19:01,047 --> 00:19:02,924
And they also keep people in.

293
00:19:03,927 --> 00:19:05,963
I'll need the password, Jack.

294
00:19:07,287 --> 00:19:08,879
Lark.

295
00:19:11,087 --> 00:19:14,477
Lark. It's the name of our boat.

296
00:19:14,647 --> 00:19:16,046
All right.

297
00:19:16,927 --> 00:19:18,155
Untie them.

298
00:19:26,287 --> 00:19:27,800
JACK:
Take it easy.

299
00:19:27,967 --> 00:19:29,719
Daddy.

300
00:19:29,887 --> 00:19:31,479
I'll be fine.

301
00:19:32,647 --> 00:19:36,196
COX: Hi, this is Jack Stanfield,
account number 51216.

302
00:19:36,367 --> 00:19:39,882
I need to change our alarm code
and give you a new password.

303
00:19:40,287 --> 00:19:44,678
I know it's difficult for you,
but try and get some sleep.

304
00:19:53,087 --> 00:19:54,805
Mom, what's going on?

305
00:19:54,967 --> 00:19:58,482
- What do they want?
- I don't know, sweetheart.

306
00:20:08,087 --> 00:20:10,237
Do you want something to eat, Jack?

307
00:20:15,127 --> 00:20:18,039
- I'm not hungry.
- No?

308
00:20:20,127 --> 00:20:22,516
Do you have any wine?

309
00:20:26,287 --> 00:20:28,437
There's some in the bar.

310
00:20:30,927 --> 00:20:34,283
COX:
Pim, go and get me a nice bottle of red.

311
00:20:34,447 --> 00:20:37,678
I don't know shit about wine, man.
How do I know if it's nice?

312
00:20:37,847 --> 00:20:40,077
Lt'll be dusty.

313
00:20:42,487 --> 00:20:44,876
I didn't know he had a gun.

314
00:20:45,367 --> 00:20:47,403
They hit him so hard.

315
00:20:48,927 --> 00:20:50,645
He'll be fine.

316
00:20:50,967 --> 00:20:53,527
It's just a little lump on the head.

317
00:20:56,127 --> 00:20:59,881
- Let's think about something nice, okay?
- Okay.

318
00:21:00,567 --> 00:21:02,125
I know.

319
00:21:04,407 --> 00:21:06,398
We're onboard the Lark.

320
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,444
And the sail's up.

321
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:12,323
And the sun is shining.

322
00:21:13,247 --> 00:21:15,044
And it's warm.

323
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:18,758
And, Andy, you're at the wheel
with your dad.

324
00:21:23,927 --> 00:21:25,485
Vel.

325
00:21:26,847 --> 00:21:28,075
Get Jack a blanket.

326
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:31,597
COX:
He's got a busy day tomorrow.

327
00:22:08,607 --> 00:22:12,077
She's asleep. Get some yourself.

328
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:15,478
- I'll wake you in an hour.
- Okay.

329
00:22:30,287 --> 00:22:32,562
MAN [OVER TV]: Let's take a look,
show you what's going on.

330
00:22:32,727 --> 00:22:35,446
Yeah, we do have a big storm,
big section of the country.

331
00:22:35,607 --> 00:22:37,484
It's gonna bring a variety
of weather...

332
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:39,399
COX:
Morning, Jack.

333
00:22:40,887 --> 00:22:42,923
Time to get ready for work.

334
00:22:43,087 --> 00:22:45,237
MAN [OVER TV]: You can look
for some snow by tomorrow...

335
00:22:45,407 --> 00:22:47,125
...through the upper Great Lakes.

336
00:22:49,047 --> 00:22:51,925
You have to do whatever they want.
I don't care what it is.

337
00:22:52,087 --> 00:22:55,284
It may not be that easy.
We've seen their faces.

338
00:22:55,447 --> 00:22:58,757
- But he said if we just cooperate...
- I know what they said, Beth.

339
00:23:00,687 --> 00:23:04,441
VOICE [OVER TV]: Did you ever notice
how big squirrels ' teeth are?

340
00:23:04,607 --> 00:23:06,165
Where's Andy?

341
00:23:06,327 --> 00:23:07,965
Breakfast.

342
00:23:08,727 --> 00:23:11,924
COX: Count to three.
AND Y: One, two, three.

343
00:23:12,447 --> 00:23:14,324
- Whoa!
JACK: Andy!

344
00:23:14,487 --> 00:23:15,966
Andy.

345
00:23:16,487 --> 00:23:18,398
This man is not our friend. Stay away.

346
00:23:18,567 --> 00:23:20,637
- But I want a pancake.
- Go see your mom.

347
00:23:20,807 --> 00:23:22,957
- Want some Cheerios?
AND Y: No.

348
00:23:24,567 --> 00:23:27,286
You're worried I'll give him
peanut oil, Jack.

349
00:23:28,047 --> 00:23:29,526
I know about his allergy.

350
00:23:30,007 --> 00:23:32,202
Don't imagine for one second...

351
00:23:32,367 --> 00:23:35,439
...that I just blundered in here
out of the rain.

352
00:23:35,607 --> 00:23:36,801
Don't touch him.

353
00:23:36,967 --> 00:23:38,400
Don't talk to him.

354
00:23:38,567 --> 00:23:40,762
And don't feed him anything.

355
00:23:47,127 --> 00:23:49,687
VEL: I'm fitting you
with two separate systems.

356
00:23:49,847 --> 00:23:51,599
Audio transmitter.

357
00:23:51,767 --> 00:23:54,327
We hear everything you do.

358
00:23:54,487 --> 00:23:57,684
- What do I do when I get to the office?
COX: You do your work, Jack.

359
00:23:58,167 --> 00:24:00,078
Chase that American dream.

360
00:24:01,127 --> 00:24:03,436
The video camera,
with a wide-angle lens.

361
00:24:04,527 --> 00:24:06,324
VEL: We see what you see.
- Whoa!

362
00:24:06,727 --> 00:24:08,126
VEL:
I've cloned your cell phone.

363
00:24:08,287 --> 00:24:11,643
Any call that you make or receive,
we can monitor.

364
00:24:12,287 --> 00:24:15,757
JACK: What about my family?
- Oh, they'll be safe...

365
00:24:15,927 --> 00:24:17,406
...here with us.

366
00:24:18,167 --> 00:24:20,078
Now, tuck your shirt in
and go to work.

367
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:31,923
- Bye, pal.
- Bye, Dad.

368
00:24:52,367 --> 00:24:53,516
You're a young man.

369
00:24:55,527 --> 00:24:57,802
JACK:
You don't need to be doing this.

370
00:25:00,407 --> 00:25:02,841
The longer it goes on...

371
00:25:03,007 --> 00:25:04,440
...the deeper in you are.

372
00:25:04,607 --> 00:25:07,917
Let's stop it right now,
before it gets worse.

373
00:25:13,247 --> 00:25:15,203
Same to you, kid.

374
00:25:19,167 --> 00:25:20,646
[CHATTERING]

375
00:25:35,247 --> 00:25:36,396
You're gonna love me.

376
00:25:36,567 --> 00:25:40,845
- Those tickets I couldn't get? I got them.
JACK: I need five minutes.

377
00:26:16,127 --> 00:26:18,561
WOMAN'S VOICE [OVER PHONE]:
The Dow Jones Industrial Average...

378
00:26:18,727 --> 00:26:20,399
...is up 16 points to 10,255...

379
00:26:20,567 --> 00:26:22,956
...on a volume of 22 million shares.

380
00:26:23,127 --> 00:26:25,357
The NASD AQ Composite
is up 11 points...

381
00:26:25,527 --> 00:26:29,281
...to 2,061 on a volume
of 1. 6 million shares.

382
00:27:09,367 --> 00:27:11,244
Can you hear me?

383
00:27:12,407 --> 00:27:13,965
JACK [OVER RADIO]:
Can you hear me?

384
00:27:15,007 --> 00:27:18,167
If you can hear me, tell your boss
I wanna speak to him.

385
00:27:18,167 --> 00:27:21,921
Tell him to quit dicking me around
and tell me what he wants me to do.

386
00:27:22,087 --> 00:27:24,920
- Can you hear me?
- Jack? Are you okay?

387
00:27:25,767 --> 00:27:28,725
Yes, I'm just talking to myself.
What's up?

388
00:27:29,247 --> 00:27:30,646
Arlin wants to see you.

389
00:27:32,767 --> 00:27:34,325
Yeah.

390
00:27:44,247 --> 00:27:46,920
So you're an architect.

391
00:27:47,847 --> 00:27:49,166
Yes.

392
00:27:50,007 --> 00:27:52,237
VEL:
And you designed this house.

393
00:27:53,447 --> 00:27:55,039
I did.

394
00:27:57,247 --> 00:27:58,885
It's nice.

395
00:28:01,207 --> 00:28:02,799
Thanks.

396
00:28:02,967 --> 00:28:04,480
How old is it?

397
00:28:04,647 --> 00:28:06,000
BETH:
Seven years.

398
00:28:06,167 --> 00:28:07,964
VEL:
How much does a house like this go for?

399
00:28:08,127 --> 00:28:10,163
This is about robbing the bank,
isn't it?

400
00:28:10,327 --> 00:28:13,687
You're using Jack to help you
rob the bank.

401
00:28:13,687 --> 00:28:15,723
Open a few doors
and press a few buttons.

402
00:28:15,887 --> 00:28:17,525
LIAM:
Just look after the kids, Beth.

403
00:28:18,487 --> 00:28:21,285
And, Vel, stick to your work.

404
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:30,559
I need you to try and get along.

405
00:28:30,727 --> 00:28:34,561
Arlin, I'm tired of him patronizing me.
Gary is an idiot.

406
00:28:34,727 --> 00:28:36,683
Be that as it may, he's a fact of life...

407
00:28:36,847 --> 00:28:40,237
...on top of which, you may be working
for him in a couple of weeks.

408
00:28:41,647 --> 00:28:43,922
Okay. I'll take care of it.

409
00:28:44,087 --> 00:28:45,805
Jack. Are you okay?

410
00:28:45,967 --> 00:28:48,083
Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.

411
00:28:48,247 --> 00:28:49,839
And Beth and the kids?

412
00:28:52,727 --> 00:28:54,160
They're fine, Arlin.

413
00:28:55,767 --> 00:28:58,406
Listen, Jack, Gary doesn't like you
very much...

414
00:28:58,567 --> 00:29:02,003
...and based on your performance
yesterday, it's not hard to understand.

415
00:29:02,167 --> 00:29:05,284
Also, we had a debt collector here
yesterday asking questions.

416
00:29:05,447 --> 00:29:08,280
- What was that all about?
- Somebody compromised my identity...

417
00:29:08,447 --> 00:29:11,280
...and ran up $95,000 worth
of online gambling debt.

418
00:29:11,807 --> 00:29:13,684
Harry's taking care of it.

419
00:29:14,687 --> 00:29:16,006
You know me, l...

420
00:29:16,167 --> 00:29:19,045
I don't gamble. I don't have any debt.

421
00:29:19,207 --> 00:29:20,401
Talk to Gary now.

422
00:29:20,567 --> 00:29:23,764
- I want this merger to go smoothly.
- I can't today, I'm...

423
00:29:23,927 --> 00:29:25,804
Today, Jack.

424
00:29:25,967 --> 00:29:28,879
Okay. I'll take care of it. Thanks.

425
00:29:29,447 --> 00:29:30,926
Are we on for dinner next week?

426
00:29:33,207 --> 00:29:35,926
Um, yeah, let me check with Beth.

427
00:29:39,207 --> 00:29:41,357
Looks good. Get it out there.

428
00:29:46,327 --> 00:29:47,965
Gary?

429
00:29:48,127 --> 00:29:50,163
Oh, yeah, Jack. Need something?

430
00:29:50,327 --> 00:29:52,682
Yeah, I just wanted to have a word.

431
00:29:52,847 --> 00:29:54,599
Lf...

432
00:29:54,807 --> 00:29:58,163
If I seemed like I was a little abrupt...

433
00:29:58,327 --> 00:30:00,887
...or difficult yesterday,
I wanna apologize.

434
00:30:01,047 --> 00:30:04,244
I want you to know I am committed
to this process.

435
00:30:05,487 --> 00:30:09,719
- Just having a bad day, that's all.
- Seem a little stressed. Everything okay?

436
00:30:09,887 --> 00:30:12,959
- Yeah. I'm just fine, Gary. Thank you.
- You sure?

437
00:30:15,127 --> 00:30:17,163
- Yeah.
- We can make this merger work...

438
00:30:17,327 --> 00:30:19,124
...for everyone's benefit.

439
00:30:19,287 --> 00:30:23,166
I'm here to help. If you ever do have
a problem, my door is always open.

440
00:30:23,327 --> 00:30:24,555
Thank you, Gary.

441
00:30:38,847 --> 00:30:41,315
Janet? Come in here
for a second, will you?

442
00:30:43,087 --> 00:30:44,884
We'll do some letters.

443
00:30:50,447 --> 00:30:54,486
Janet, if I've been difficult
or distant...

444
00:30:54,647 --> 00:30:56,922
...for the last couple of days,
I hope you'll understand.

445
00:30:57,087 --> 00:30:59,317
JACK [OVER RADIO]: I wanna apologize.
JANET [OVER RADIO]: That's okay.

446
00:30:59,487 --> 00:31:01,284
JACK:
We're a team, you and me.

447
00:31:01,647 --> 00:31:06,641
And I want you to understand how much
I appreciate what you do for me.

448
00:31:06,807 --> 00:31:09,640
- Thanks, Jack.
- It means the world to me.

449
00:31:11,607 --> 00:31:13,996
JACK [OVER RADIO]:
Sometimes I think I just need to...

450
00:31:15,887 --> 00:31:17,559
...relax.

451
00:31:17,727 --> 00:31:19,240
Okay.

452
00:31:19,407 --> 00:31:20,681
- Take a minute.
- Okay.

453
00:31:20,847 --> 00:31:23,077
Take five minutes out of the day...

454
00:31:23,327 --> 00:31:27,605
...and just sit quietly
and take a break.

455
00:31:28,167 --> 00:31:31,716
JACK [OVER RADIO]: You know, just...
JANET [OVER RADIO]: Sure. Jack...?

456
00:31:38,367 --> 00:31:40,403
He's lost it. Completely lost it.

457
00:31:40,567 --> 00:31:42,523
Letter to Scott Smith.

458
00:31:42,687 --> 00:31:45,918
Dear Scott,
pursuant to your request...

459
00:31:46,127 --> 00:31:49,278
...for further information regarding
the security-interface issues...

460
00:31:49,447 --> 00:31:52,757
...unfortunately, the information
that you requested is not available.

461
00:31:52,927 --> 00:31:54,485
Sorry for the inconvenience.

462
00:31:54,647 --> 00:31:56,558
Until the merger...

463
00:31:56,727 --> 00:31:59,480
Shit. Strike that.

464
00:31:59,647 --> 00:32:02,798
- Harry's in L.A. For a convention.
- Thanks for coming to tell me that.

465
00:32:02,967 --> 00:32:05,879
JACK: I can refer you
to my associate, Gary Mitchell...

466
00:32:06,047 --> 00:32:08,845
...who may be able to provide you
with the information.

467
00:32:09,167 --> 00:32:11,283
- Regards to the family, usual close.
- Jack?

468
00:32:11,927 --> 00:32:13,918
JANET [OVER RADIO]:
Jack, I've been looking for you.

469
00:32:14,087 --> 00:32:15,566
Shit.

470
00:32:15,727 --> 00:32:17,877
JANET [OVER RADIO]:
There's a Bill Redmond to see you.

471
00:32:18,087 --> 00:32:19,202
- Shit!
JACK [OVER RADIO]: Who?

472
00:32:19,367 --> 00:32:21,597
Redmond,
from the Federal Banking Board?

473
00:32:21,767 --> 00:32:25,157
- What are you talking about, Federal...?
- Jack Stanfield?

474
00:32:26,127 --> 00:32:28,243
Bill Redmond. Pleased to meet you.

475
00:32:30,367 --> 00:32:32,722
Janet, close the door, please.

476
00:32:35,167 --> 00:32:37,920
- Look...
- Oh, Jack, Jack, Jack.

477
00:32:39,607 --> 00:32:43,395
Liam, take the boy downstairs
and break his knee.

478
00:32:43,567 --> 00:32:44,716
Don't do that.

479
00:32:44,887 --> 00:32:46,957
It's my fault, not his. It's my mistake.

480
00:32:47,127 --> 00:32:48,242
Don't take it out on the boy.

481
00:32:48,407 --> 00:32:49,760
[AND Y SCREAMING OVER PHONE]

482
00:32:49,967 --> 00:32:51,320
