by the time you get here.

734
00:52:58,247 --> 00:53:00,841
I guess I never thought
we'd pull this off.

735
00:53:01,007 --> 00:53:03,316
I know. What time
does your flight get in? I'll pick you up.

736
00:53:42,607 --> 00:53:43,926
Fire her.

737
00:53:44,887 --> 00:53:46,559
What?

738
00:53:47,767 --> 00:53:50,406
Fire Janet? Why?

739
00:53:50,567 --> 00:53:52,876
I don't like the way she looks at me.

740
00:53:53,047 --> 00:53:54,605
Fire her.

741
00:53:56,567 --> 00:53:58,159
- Anything else?
- I'm good. Thanks.

742
00:53:58,327 --> 00:54:01,205
- You're the only banker who drinks tea.
- I am?

743
00:54:01,367 --> 00:54:03,403
Give us a minute, will you?

744
00:54:13,687 --> 00:54:17,600
Janet, I want you to pack up your stuff
and go home.

745
00:54:17,767 --> 00:54:19,758
What? What do you mean?

746
00:54:20,927 --> 00:54:22,565
Just what I said.

747
00:54:23,047 --> 00:54:25,117
Pack up your stuff and go home.

748
00:54:26,047 --> 00:54:27,241
Why?

749
00:54:28,087 --> 00:54:29,839
You're fired.

750
00:54:30,487 --> 00:54:33,524
- Lf this is a joke, it's not funny, Jack.
- No, this is not a joke.

751
00:54:33,687 --> 00:54:37,362
I'll call Human Resources. I'll get you
a job with somebody else at the bank.

752
00:54:37,527 --> 00:54:40,687
- Right now, just do what I said.
- What are you talking about?

753
00:54:40,687 --> 00:54:42,962
- Is this because of him?
- Don't argue with me.

754
00:54:43,127 --> 00:54:48,645
- But I haven't done anything wrong.
- Pack up your shit and get out of here.

755
00:54:48,807 --> 00:54:50,399
Now.

756
00:54:50,647 --> 00:54:52,842
Screw you, Jack.

757
00:55:00,527 --> 00:55:01,960
When is Daddy coming home?

758
00:55:05,687 --> 00:55:08,804
As soon as he can get them
some money from the bank.

759
00:55:08,967 --> 00:55:10,844
And then they'll leave?

760
00:55:11,007 --> 00:55:12,599
And then they'll leave.

761
00:55:16,327 --> 00:55:18,682
MAN [OVER TV]: It was a good knife
when you first got it.

762
00:55:18,847 --> 00:55:20,758
Maybe six months later, it got dull.

763
00:55:20,927 --> 00:55:22,519
Ever try to cut a tomato with these?

764
00:55:22,687 --> 00:55:25,121
Cox is gonna kill you.
You know that, don't you?

765
00:55:25,287 --> 00:55:27,278
BETH:
Just like Willy.

766
00:55:27,447 --> 00:55:28,880
Willy made mistakes.

767
00:55:29,047 --> 00:55:31,083
You think he'll reward you
because you're good?

768
00:55:31,247 --> 00:55:32,919
- Shut up.
BETH: Soon as he has the money...

769
00:55:33,087 --> 00:55:35,760
...you'll be no more use to him.
- Go back into the bedroom.

770
00:55:37,727 --> 00:55:40,446
He has no reason
to let any of you live.

771
00:55:45,807 --> 00:55:48,605
What I'm asking for isn't standard,
you know.

772
00:55:50,247 --> 00:55:51,726
They might not do it.

773
00:55:51,887 --> 00:55:53,479
They might say:

774
00:55:54,127 --> 00:55:56,766
"We did it yesterday" or "It's scheduled
for tomorrow" or something.

775
00:55:56,927 --> 00:55:59,725
Get on with it. Make it happen.

776
00:56:11,447 --> 00:56:14,644
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]: Operations.
- Stacy, Jack Stanfield in Seattle.

777
00:56:14,807 --> 00:56:16,479
Hi, Mr. Stanfield.

778
00:56:16,647 --> 00:56:18,683
I need you to run
a maintenance sort program...

779
00:56:18,847 --> 00:56:21,520
...weigh all online accounts,
largest to smallest.

780
00:56:21,687 --> 00:56:23,643
Give me a sec, I'll check.

781
00:56:25,487 --> 00:56:26,636
Okay, keycard.

782
00:56:27,367 --> 00:56:29,961
Coming up. There you go.

783
00:56:30,767 --> 00:56:32,598
Ready to run.

784
00:56:32,767 --> 00:56:35,600
GARY: I'm telling you, Arlin...
- Go and deal with it.

785
00:56:36,527 --> 00:56:37,880
JACK:
It's running, Stacy.

786
00:56:38,047 --> 00:56:40,720
- Okay, if you need...
- Go.

787
00:56:42,807 --> 00:56:44,240
[PEOPLE SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

788
00:56:44,767 --> 00:56:46,485
GARY:
With money moving every nanosecond...

789
00:56:46,647 --> 00:56:48,842
...we have to provide a platform
for technology...

790
00:56:49,007 --> 00:56:51,840
...to be able to maintain
and control risk.

791
00:56:52,247 --> 00:56:54,397
GARY: You have to be
thinking outside the box.

792
00:56:54,567 --> 00:56:55,966
ARLIN:
Oh, I understand.

793
00:56:56,127 --> 00:56:59,802
These geeks with their laptops can figure
out ways to steal money from you.

794
00:56:59,967 --> 00:57:02,322
- Arlin, you lost?
- Hi, Jack.

795
00:57:02,487 --> 00:57:05,843
No, Gary's trying to teach me something
about the new technology.

796
00:57:06,007 --> 00:57:07,156
- Well, good luck.
- Yeah.

797
00:57:07,327 --> 00:57:10,205
I told him you've been trying that
for years. What are you up to?

798
00:57:10,367 --> 00:57:11,925
Well, there's a...

799
00:57:12,087 --> 00:57:14,203
I came down because there was...

800
00:57:14,367 --> 00:57:16,403
