with one of the servers.

801
00:57:16,567 --> 00:57:18,205
Got the engineers coming down.

802
00:57:18,367 --> 00:57:20,881
I asked to be notified
about all maintenance issues.

803
00:57:21,047 --> 00:57:23,720
GARY:
No one told me a server was down.

804
00:57:23,927 --> 00:57:27,283
They probably didn't realize procedures
changed. Wichita didn't call you?

805
00:57:27,447 --> 00:57:28,846
No.

806
00:57:29,007 --> 00:57:29,996
Who's "they"?

807
00:57:30,167 --> 00:57:31,156
[BANGING NOISE]

808
00:57:31,367 --> 00:57:33,562
I don't know. Janet took the call.

809
00:57:33,727 --> 00:57:35,604
Did you fire her this morning?

810
00:57:35,767 --> 00:57:37,837
You know, Arlin,
it just wasn't working out.

811
00:57:38,007 --> 00:57:39,963
Seems kind of sudden.

812
00:57:40,247 --> 00:57:43,478
Um, well, actually, it's been...

813
00:57:45,247 --> 00:57:47,397
It's been building for a while.

814
00:57:47,567 --> 00:57:51,799
Well, care to join us?
Help Gary unlock my analog brain?

815
00:57:51,967 --> 00:57:54,640
I think I'd better get back
to the office.

816
00:57:58,127 --> 00:58:00,038
I'll check with you later.

817
00:58:01,287 --> 00:58:03,960
GARY: All right, Arlin, you gotta
understand two things:

818
00:58:04,127 --> 00:58:07,437
- Number one, analog is for sissies.
ARLIN: So I gathered.

819
00:58:36,967 --> 00:58:38,286
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

820
00:58:39,407 --> 00:58:41,398
[FOOTSTEPS]

821
00:58:45,447 --> 00:58:47,005
[MAN COUGHS]

822
00:58:48,647 --> 00:58:49,875
[TOILET FLUSHES]

823
00:58:50,567 --> 00:58:51,556
[DOOR OPENS, CLOSES]

824
00:58:55,087 --> 00:58:57,203
COX:
He didn't wash his hands.

825
00:58:57,367 --> 00:59:00,200
That's why you should never eat
peanuts off a bar.

826
00:59:03,327 --> 00:59:04,885
JACK:
Let's go.

827
00:59:21,927 --> 00:59:23,997
Can I take his collar off?

828
00:59:24,567 --> 00:59:27,286
- No, honey. He needs that.
- Beth, come with me, please.

829
00:59:28,487 --> 00:59:30,478
- Where?
LIAM: Just downstairs.

830
00:59:30,647 --> 00:59:32,239
Mom.

831
00:59:32,407 --> 00:59:34,637
BETH: It's okay. I'll be right back.
- Now, Beth.

832
00:59:36,727 --> 00:59:37,876
Why do you hate us so much?

833
00:59:38,047 --> 00:59:42,006
I don't hate you, Sarah.
I just don't care about you.

834
00:59:45,847 --> 00:59:48,156
I need you to make a call.

835
00:59:51,647 --> 00:59:54,605
Why...? Why would I say this?

836
00:59:56,887 --> 00:59:58,843
Make him believe you.

837
01:00:12,127 --> 01:00:14,322
MAN:
Well, hopefully, that's the way...

838
01:00:19,207 --> 01:00:20,560
[DOOR BUZZES]

839
01:00:22,807 --> 01:00:24,365
COX [WHISPERING]:
Which one is he?

840
01:00:25,247 --> 01:00:27,442
JACK [WHISPERING]:
The kid in the blue shirt.

841
01:00:32,367 --> 01:00:34,005
Come here.

842
01:00:38,007 --> 01:00:39,998
Mr. Stanfield, sir?
Why did Janet get fired?

843
01:00:40,167 --> 01:00:42,761
- She didn't do anything.
- We know what you're up to, Bobby.

844
01:00:42,927 --> 01:00:44,565
What I'm up to?
What do you mean?

845
01:00:44,727 --> 01:00:47,844
You and Janet have made repeated
attempts to access secure information.

846
01:00:48,007 --> 01:00:49,235
No, that's ridiculous.

847
01:00:49,407 --> 01:00:52,080
She rolled over on you, Bobby.
She gave you up.

848
01:00:52,247 --> 01:00:53,680
