908
01:07:57,367 --> 01:07:58,925
Yeah, we're leaving now.

909
01:07:59,087 --> 01:08:00,725
I'll meet you when I'm done.

910
01:08:01,407 --> 01:08:03,125
Yeah, will do.

911
01:08:03,447 --> 01:08:05,358
- Cox says goodbye.
- Are they alive?

912
01:08:05,527 --> 01:08:07,245
Just tell me that. Are they alive?

913
01:08:07,407 --> 01:08:09,762
- Come on, man, talk to me.
- We're leaving now, Jack.

914
01:08:09,927 --> 01:08:12,122
Why? Just kill me here.
Why should I make it easy?

915
01:08:12,287 --> 01:08:14,755
You still think there's a chance
you might be able to help them.

916
01:08:14,927 --> 01:08:15,916
Now, let's go.

917
01:09:05,767 --> 01:09:07,325
[PHONE RINGING]

918
01:09:12,527 --> 01:09:15,200
HARRY'S VOICE [OVER MACHINE]:
Hi, it's Harry. Leave a message.

919
01:09:16,047 --> 01:09:19,357
JACK [OVER MACHINE]:
Harry. Jesus, Harry, where are you?

920
01:09:19,807 --> 01:09:23,322
I'm in trouble. I'm in real trouble.

921
01:09:23,487 --> 01:09:25,079
I need...

922
01:09:25,247 --> 01:09:26,600
I need to talk to you.

923
01:09:26,767 --> 01:09:28,564
Call me on my... No, you can't.

924
01:09:28,727 --> 01:09:30,319
You can't call me on my cell.

925
01:09:30,487 --> 01:09:32,364
They're listening.

926
01:09:32,847 --> 01:09:34,485
Shit.

927
01:09:55,847 --> 01:09:58,156
WOMAN:
It's really coming down, huh?

928
01:10:01,487 --> 01:10:04,638
JACK: What a night.
- Well, it is Seattle.

929
01:11:25,847 --> 01:11:29,317
JACK'S VOICE [OVER MACHINE]:
Harry. Jesus, Harry, where are you?

930
01:11:29,487 --> 01:11:32,126
I'm in trouble. I'm in real trouble.

931
01:11:32,287 --> 01:11:33,640
I need to talk to you.

932
01:11:33,807 --> 01:11:36,844
Call me on my... No, you can 't.
You can 't call me on my cell.

933
01:11:38,607 --> 01:11:40,245
They're listening. Shit.

934
01:11:41,967 --> 01:11:43,878
WOMAN [OVER MACHINE]:
This is Dr. Hay's office...

935
01:11:44,047 --> 01:11:47,562
...confirming your 8 a.m. Appointment
Monday. We'll see you then. Thank you.

936
01:11:48,447 --> 01:11:51,607
BETH'S VOICE [OVER MACHINE]:
Harry, I did it. I finally left him.

937
01:11:51,607 --> 01:11:53,996
God, I love you so much.

938
01:11:54,167 --> 01:11:59,480
I'm afraid. Get out of there, okay?
Come as soon as you can.

939
01:12:00,367 --> 01:12:02,358
I love you.

940
01:12:02,767 --> 01:12:04,917
MAN'S VOICE [OVER MACHINE]:
Harry, it's Eric at Redline.

941
01:12:05,087 --> 01:12:08,796
I found a guy who 's selling those
Porsche 356 parts you...

942
01:12:09,007 --> 01:12:10,360
[DOOR OPENING]

943
01:12:11,567 --> 01:12:13,205
HARRY:
Yeah, come on in.

944
01:12:13,367 --> 01:12:14,880
COX:
Thank you.

945
01:12:16,527 --> 01:12:18,358
Wow, quite a place.

946
01:12:18,727 --> 01:12:20,718
HARRY:
Yeah. I wanted something...

947
01:12:20,887 --> 01:12:22,878
...sort of Dean Martin-ish,
you know what I mean?

948
01:12:23,287 --> 01:12:24,436
COX:
Well, you nailed it.

949
01:12:24,607 --> 01:12:26,040
You know, I had my doubts.

950
01:12:26,207 --> 01:12:27,435
But after our meeting...

951
01:12:27,607 --> 01:12:30,644
...I could tell Jack was
definitely interested.

952
01:12:30,847 --> 01:12:32,326
And the timing was perfect.

953
01:12:32,487 --> 01:12:35,638
Without the merger, Jack would
never consider leaving the bank...

954
01:12:35,807 --> 01:12:37,684
...and starting up on his own.

955
01:12:37,847 --> 01:12:39,724
HARRY: How about a beer?
COX: No, I'm good.

956
01:12:39,887 --> 01:12:43,596
HARRY: Once Jack gets his teeth into it,
there'll be no stopping him.

957
01:12:43,767 --> 01:12:45,962
Thanks for pulling that proposal
together so fast.

958
01:12:46,487 --> 01:12:48,045
COX:
I think I will have that beer.

959
01:12:48,247 --> 01:12:49,236
HARRY:
You bet.

960
01:12:49,407 --> 01:12:50,760
[GUNSHOT]

961
01:13:07,127 --> 01:13:09,038
JACK:
Harry?

962
01:13:09,207 --> 01:13:10,799
Harry?

963
01:13:13,087 --> 01:13:14,964
Oh, Jesus.

964
01:13:31,447 --> 01:13:33,165
Sure it wasn't the TV, Mrs. Levy?

965
01:13:33,327 --> 01:13:35,079
WOMAN [OVER PHONE]:
No, it wasn 't the damn TV.

966
01:13:35,247 --> 01:13:37,078
I'm telling you,
the guy had a gun in his hand.

967
01:13:37,247 --> 01:13:38,646
Okay, what'd the guy look like?

968
01:13:38,807 --> 01:13:41,367
He was wearing a gray suit with,
like, a necktie.

969
01:13:50,207 --> 01:13:51,560
[WHISTLES]

970
01:13:52,807 --> 01:13:54,365
Shit.

971
01:13:56,727 --> 01:13:58,319
Taxi.

972
01:13:58,847 --> 01:14:01,202
Hey, taxi! Taxi!

973
01:14:19,767 --> 01:14:22,964
WOMAN:
