[SPEAKING IN ASIAN LANGUAGE]

977
01:14:28,647 --> 01:14:31,115
- Janet Stone. She...
- Oh, uh...

978
01:14:31,567 --> 01:14:33,239
- Thank you.
- Over there.

979
01:14:33,407 --> 01:14:34,601
Janet.

980
01:14:34,767 --> 01:14:37,998
- Janet. Janet, let me in, please.
- What are you doing here?

981
01:14:38,167 --> 01:14:40,601
- Get out of here, Jack. You're crazy!
JACK: Let me in.

982
01:14:40,767 --> 01:14:42,803
Get out!

983
01:14:46,647 --> 01:14:49,684
Listen to me. Listen to me.
Listen to me.

984
01:14:49,847 --> 01:14:51,485
The man who was in my office.

985
01:14:51,647 --> 01:14:54,286
Mr. Redmond. He's a bank robber.

986
01:14:54,447 --> 01:14:57,598
He's got Beth and the kids.
He's gonna kill them.

987
01:14:57,767 --> 01:14:59,678
They may be dead already.
I need your help.

988
01:14:59,847 --> 01:15:03,920
Do you understand me?
I need your help to try and save them.

989
01:15:04,687 --> 01:15:06,086
Okay.

990
01:15:06,487 --> 01:15:09,047
- I understand.
- Don't scream.

991
01:15:16,087 --> 01:15:18,317
- Sorry.
- Shouldn't we call the police?

992
01:15:21,647 --> 01:15:23,603
No. No police.

993
01:15:24,207 --> 01:15:25,401
What about Harry?

994
01:15:27,967 --> 01:15:29,195
Harry's dead.

995
01:15:30,047 --> 01:15:32,117
Jesus.

996
01:15:34,727 --> 01:15:37,116
I was at Harry's apartment
when Cox...

997
01:15:37,287 --> 01:15:39,847
...or Redmond, whatever his name is,
shot him.

998
01:15:40,007 --> 01:15:42,396
People there saw me
with a gun in my hand.

999
01:15:42,567 --> 01:15:45,161
There's a dead man in my house.

1000
01:15:45,327 --> 01:15:46,999
By the time I explain to the police...

1001
01:15:48,567 --> 01:15:51,240
...Beth and the kids could be dead.
- God.

1002
01:15:51,447 --> 01:15:53,199
I need you to help me find Bobby.

1003
01:15:53,367 --> 01:15:55,244
- Bobby? Why?
- I need his cell phone.

1004
01:15:55,407 --> 01:15:58,160
I used his phone to photograph
some account code numbers.

1005
01:15:58,327 --> 01:16:01,285
I've gotta have it to get the money back.
Can you help me?

1006
01:16:01,447 --> 01:16:03,881
Yeah. I'll find his number.

1007
01:16:22,407 --> 01:16:25,638
VEL: Why can't you get
a rare burger anymore?

1008
01:16:25,807 --> 01:16:26,956
PIM:
E. Coli.

1009
01:16:27,127 --> 01:16:28,560
[LAUGHING]

1010
01:16:30,167 --> 01:16:32,840
- Everything all right?
- Yeah. Did you talk to Liam?

1011
01:16:33,007 --> 01:16:36,556
- No, not yet.
- Where the hell is he, man?

1012
01:16:36,887 --> 01:16:38,525
- Let's go.
- Now?

1013
01:16:38,687 --> 01:16:40,405
Yeah, now!

1014
01:16:41,927 --> 01:16:43,155
Shit.

1015
01:16:43,847 --> 01:16:46,156
You guys need to go
to the washroom?

1016
01:16:46,807 --> 01:16:48,877
Don't say I didn't ask.

1017
01:16:57,487 --> 01:16:58,966
Jack.

1018
01:16:59,327 --> 01:17:01,204
- Jesus.
- I found Bobby.

1019
01:17:01,367 --> 01:17:02,356
Oh, great.

1020
01:17:02,527 --> 01:17:03,755
[PHONE RINGING]

1021
01:17:06,607 --> 01:17:09,644
- It's Cox.
- Are you gonna answer?

1022
01:17:10,807 --> 01:17:15,403
I'm not ready to talk to him yet.
I need Bobby's cell phone first.

1023
01:17:15,687 --> 01:17:18,565
- And I'll need your laptop.
- No problem.

1024
01:17:18,727 --> 01:17:22,276
- And can we use your car?
- Problem.

1025
01:17:23,207 --> 01:17:25,243
Pop it! Pop it! Pop the clutch!

1026
01:17:26,647 --> 01:17:29,036
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

1027
01:17:31,687 --> 01:17:32,881
Keep the gas up.

1028
01:17:46,967 --> 01:17:49,686
I can't believe Harry's dead.

1029
01:17:51,287 --> 01:17:53,164
Was he involved with Cox?

1030
01:17:53,327 --> 01:17:54,999
No.

1031
01:17:57,647 --> 01:18:00,559
No. Harry thought
he was a businessman.

1032
01:18:01,047 --> 01:18:04,084
But didn't Harry introduce you to Cox?

1033
01:18:04,247 --> 01:18:05,999
The whole...

1034
01:18:06,887 --> 01:18:09,526
...investment thing was just a scam.

1035
01:18:10,367 --> 01:18:14,155
Cox was using Harry to get next to me.
Harry didn't know about the robbery.

1036
01:18:15,207 --> 01:18:17,038
Cox killed him with my gun...

1037
01:18:17,207 --> 01:18:21,758
...to make it look as if I shot him
in a jealous rage over Beth.

1038
01:18:21,927 --> 01:18:24,600
Harry and Beth? Give me a break.

1039
01:18:24,767 --> 01:18:30,444
He planted a message from Beth
on Harry's answering machine.

1040
01:18:33,087 --> 01:18:35,237
Saying she...

1041
01:18:37,927 --> 01:18:41,207
Saying she was leaving me.

1042
01:18:41,207 --> 01:18:46,327
I also found some encrypted files
on his computer.

1043
01:18:46,487 --> 01:18:50,321
I'm sure they'd tie him and me
together in the robbery.

1044
01:18:50,487 --> 01:18:52,876
Cox had it all planned out.

1045
01:18:53,047 --> 01:18:54,560
Even the gambling debts.

1046
01:18:55,967 --> 01:18:57,844
We hatch this plan to rob the bank...

1047
01:18:58,007 --> 01:19:00,237
...then I find out my buddy is
sleeping with my wife.

1048
01:19:00,687 --> 01:19:04,236
After the robbery, I go to his apartment,
I kill him and I...

1049
01:19:05,447 --> 01:19:08,086
I disappear with the money forever.

1050
01:19:09,527 --> 01:19:11,882
Forever, as in dead?

1051
01:19:15,047 --> 01:19:18,005
I killed the man who was
supposed to kill me.

1052
01:19:35,447 --> 01:19:37,483
Be right back.

1053
01:19:40,647 --> 01:19:42,126
[CHRISTIAN ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

1054
01:19:49,007 --> 01:19:50,326
[PHONE RINGING]

1055
01:19:59,647 --> 01:20:02,807
- What are you doing?
- I didn't tell Jack any of that stuff.

1056
01:20:02,807 --> 01:20:06,356
- Why did he say you did?
- I don't know. I'm sorry about that.

1057
01:20:06,527 --> 01:20:08,006
Can I borrow your cell phone?

1058
01:20:08,167 --> 01:20:11,284
Your cell phone, do you have it?
Can I borrow it?

1059
01:20:12,087 --> 01:20:13,566
Thanks.

1060
01:20:17,927 --> 01:20:19,838
- Here.
- Great.

1061
01:20:20,047 --> 01:20:21,446
Please let this work.

1062
01:20:32,367 --> 01:20:34,801
JACK: Here we go.
JANET: Now what?

1063
01:20:34,967 --> 01:20:37,322
I just need to find
a wire-transfer terminal.

1064
01:20:37,487 --> 01:20:40,524
Where are you gonna find
a bank open at this hour?

1065
01:20:42,847 --> 01:20:46,522
WOMAN [OVER INTERCOM]: Welcome
to Seattle-Tacoma International Airport.

1066
01:20:51,447 --> 01:20:54,086
Jack, you look like a bank robber.

1067
01:20:56,007 --> 01:20:58,282
- Keep the motor running.
- Good luck.

1068
01:20:58,967 --> 01:21:00,559
Thank you.

1069
01:21:02,007 --> 01:21:03,406
[PHONE RINGING]

1070
01:21:26,647 --> 01:21:28,558
We'll see you in the morning.

1071
01:21:31,607 --> 01:21:33,837
I'm sorry, we're closed.

1072
01:21:40,927 --> 01:21:43,600
I need to get on your
wire-transfer terminal.

1073
01:21:43,767 --> 01:21:45,246
Absolutely. I'm sorry.

1074
01:21:45,407 --> 01:21:48,479
We usually don't have
a supervisor here this late.

1075
01:21:48,647 --> 01:21:50,160
- You can use this one.
- Thank you.

1076
01:21:52,087 --> 01:21:53,600
The money is put away. L...

1077
01:21:53,767 --> 01:21:56,235
It's not about the money.
Sit down. Sit down.

1078
01:21:57,527 --> 01:21:58,926
I'm not gonna hurt you.

1079
01:22:00,087 --> 01:22:04,877
8499116...

1080
01:22:21,487 --> 01:22:22,886
[PHONE RINGING]

1081
01:22:25,407 --> 01:22:26,806
Liam, where have you been?

1082
01:22:26,967 --> 01:22:28,719
Change of plans, asshole.

1083
01:22:30,567 --> 01:22:32,717
Jack. Where are you?

1084
01:22:32,887 --> 01:22:37,039
At a bank. I just hacked
into your Cayman Island accounts.

1085
01:22:37,207 --> 01:22:39,163
- That's impossible.
- You think so?

1086
01:22:39,327 --> 01:22:43,036
I have your account details.
You just lost 20 million.

1087
01:22:43,207 --> 01:22:45,038
Bullshit.

1088
01:22:54,087 --> 01:22:55,406
What's going on?

1089
01:22:55,567 --> 01:22:56,761
Check the accounts.

1090
01:22:56,927 --> 01:22:59,646
- What for?
- Can you check the accounts, please?

1091
01:23:00,047 --> 01:23:01,799
Yeah.

1092
01:23:08,207 --> 01:23:09,686
There goes another 20 million.

1093
01:23:10,487 --> 01:23:12,159
- Come on.
- I'm going as fast as I can.

1094
01:23:13,767 --> 01:23:16,235
We're down 40 million.

1095
01:23:16,447 --> 01:23:19,678
Now you know what it feels like
to lose what you love.

1096
01:23:20,767 --> 01:23:23,201
- Another account just cleared.
- That was for Harry.

1097
01:23:23,407 --> 01:23:25,796
Your family are dead. Do you hear me?
They are dead!

1098
01:23:25,967 --> 01:23:27,878
For all I know, they're dead already.

1099
01:23:28,727 --> 01:23:30,126
He emptied another one.

1100
01:23:30,287 --> 01:23:32,084
You're down to your last 20 million.

1101
01:23:38,167 --> 01:23:40,522
- Talk to your husband.
- Jack?

1102
01:23:41,127 --> 01:23:45,166
I love you. Just do whatever you can
to save the children.

1103
01:23:45,327 --> 01:23:48,717
I am, baby. I love you too.

1104
01:23:49,247 --> 01:23:50,805
[DOG BARKING]

1105
01:23:51,167 --> 01:23:54,125
Put the money back
or I'll put a bullet through her head.

1106
01:23:54,287 --> 01:23:56,755
You do anything to her
or my children...

1107
01:23:56,927 --> 01:23:58,758
...and you don 't get a dime.

1108
01:23:58,927 --> 01:24:00,076
It's all gone.

1109
01:24:00,567 --> 01:24:02,876
Jack, calm down.
If you calm down, we can talk this...

1110
01:24:03,047 --> 01:24:05,277
You'll get the money
when I get my family.

1111
01:24:05,447 --> 01:24:08,200
Tomorrow morning, when
the banks open. I'll let you know where.

1112
01:24:08,687 --> 01:24:10,996
- Yeah, I'll be there.
- Do you hear me?

1113
01:24:11,167 --> 01:24:13,362
- I'll be there. Just...
- Don 't bother calling me.

1114
01:24:13,687 --> 01:24:16,406
Because I've got nothing to say
to you.

1115
01:24:18,367 --> 01:24:20,358
- You need to get out of here.
- What?

1116
01:24:20,527 --> 01:24:22,324
- I pushed the silent alarm.
- When?

1117
01:24:22,487 --> 01:24:25,638
A couple of minutes ago. I'm sorry.

1118
01:24:26,207 --> 01:24:27,925
PIM:
Liam was gonna take care of him.

1119
01:24:28,087 --> 01:24:29,440
Put the woman back in the van.

1120
01:24:29,607 --> 01:24:33,441
- How you gonna give me my money?!
- Put her back in the van!

1121
01:24:36,727 --> 01:24:38,160
COX:
Shut up!

1122
01:24:42,367 --> 01:24:44,085
Shit.

1123
01:24:53,527 --> 01:24:55,279
- Move it!
- Just a second. Here he is.

1124
01:24:55,447 --> 01:24:57,836
- Get out of here, now.
- Sorry.

1125
01:24:59,087 --> 01:25:00,645
What happened?

1126
01:25:01,167 --> 01:25:02,839
They're alive.

1127
01:25:03,047 --> 01:25:04,241
Thank God.

1128
01:25:04,407 --> 01:25:06,796
I just bet everything on Cox's greed.

1129
01:25:06,967 --> 01:25:08,605
I got the money.

1130
01:25:08,767 --> 01:25:10,997
So we still got a chance.

1131
01:25:11,767 --> 01:25:13,041
What are you gonna do?

1132
01:25:13,207 --> 01:25:15,926
I'm gonna meet Cox at the bank
in the morning.

1133
01:25:16,567 --> 01:25:18,762
- How are you gonna get in?
- I can't. You can.

1134
01:25:18,927 --> 01:25:20,883
You fired me, remember?
I don't have a pass.

1135
01:25:25,567 --> 01:25:28,081
Barking. Jesus, he was barking.

1136
01:25:28,247 --> 01:25:29,441
- Jack?
- He was...

1137
01:25:29,607 --> 01:25:31,279
Pull over. Pull over here.

1138
01:25:31,527 --> 01:25:32,880
[HORNS HONKING]

1139
01:25:40,207 --> 01:25:42,163
Jack, what are you doing?

1140
01:25:43,447 --> 01:25:45,358
I heard Rusty barking.

1141
01:25:45,527 --> 01:25:48,360
- He's with Beth and the kids in the van.
- So?

1142
01:25:48,527 --> 01:25:50,199
He's got this...

1143
01:25:50,607 --> 01:25:53,644
...GPS. He's got this GPS thing.

1144
01:25:53,807 --> 01:25:55,525
You're not making any sense.

1145
01:25:55,687 --> 01:25:57,678
He was running away all the time...

1146
01:25:57,847 --> 01:25:59,917
...so we got him a collar
with a GPS locator.

1147
01:26:00,207 --> 01:26:02,846
It's from this website.
If he's still got it on...

1148
01:26:06,607 --> 01:26:08,882
Got him. There they are.

1149
01:26:12,247 --> 01:26:13,521
What are they doing?

1150
01:26:13,687 --> 01:26:14,961
Driving out of town.

1151
01:26:15,127 --> 01:26:18,164
Why is he doing that?
Didn't he say he would meet you here?

1152
01:26:19,247 --> 01:26:21,602
- Here. Get in the car.
- What are you doing?

1153
01:26:22,607 --> 01:26:24,438
I'm gonna find my dog.

1154
01:26:36,607 --> 01:26:37,881
[DOG BARKING]

1155
01:26:38,487 --> 01:26:41,047
Can you shut the dog up?

1156
01:26:41,207 --> 01:26:42,640
Shh. It's okay, Rusty.

1157
01:26:45,007 --> 01:26:47,123
You know, you're never
gonna get that money now.

1158
01:26:48,167 --> 01:26:52,399
But if you turn around and take us back,
my husband'll give you what you want.

1159
01:26:52,567 --> 01:26:54,205
You can split it
between the two of you.

1160
01:26:54,367 --> 01:26:56,244
Shut the damn dog up!

1161
01:27:15,767 --> 01:27:17,359
JANET:
Jack.

1162
01:27:18,887 --> 01:27:20,764
- Are you okay?
- Yeah, I'm okay. Yeah.

1163
01:27:20,927 --> 01:27:22,758
- You want me to drive?
- No. No, I'm fine.

1164
01:27:24,047 --> 01:27:25,241
Where are they now?

1165
01:27:26,447 --> 01:27:27,641
They're still on the 2.

1166
01:27:53,847 --> 01:27:55,599
They just turned off the road.

1167
01:27:55,767 --> 01:27:59,282
There's nothing on this map except
a big lake and some railroad tracks.

1168
01:27:59,447 --> 01:28:01,642
- How far?
- Twenty miles.

1169
01:28:01,807 --> 01:28:04,321
Where the hell are they going?

1170
01:28:07,567 --> 01:28:09,478
Shut up.

1171
01:28:10,007 --> 01:28:12,885
Shut your goddamn dog up.
I swear to God.

1172
01:28:13,047 --> 01:28:14,560
Shh. It's okay, Rusty.

1173
01:28:14,727 --> 01:28:16,718
- Come here, Rusty. Come here.
PIM: Shut up!

1174
01:28:19,287 --> 01:28:21,039
That's it!

1175
01:28:21,727 --> 01:28:23,445
I warned you!

1176
01:28:24,847 --> 01:28:27,281
What are you doing? No! Rusty!

1177
01:28:27,527 --> 01:28:30,041
Shut up or you're going next!

1178
01:28:31,167 --> 01:28:33,522
- Rusty! Sorry, baby.
PIM: Quiet!

1179
01:28:33,727 --> 01:28:35,604
You hear me?

1180
01:28:37,927 --> 01:28:39,201
[CRYING]

1181
01:29:05,367 --> 01:29:06,516
Put them in the back room.

1182
01:29:06,687 --> 01:29:09,201
Maybe we should just forget it.

1183
01:29:09,367 --> 01:29:10,800
Let them all go.

1184
01:29:10,967 --> 01:29:15,040
Maybe you should do your job
and put them in the back room.

1185
01:29:26,607 --> 01:29:28,563
Why would he bring them
all the way out here?

1186
01:29:29,527 --> 01:29:34,157
I don't think he was planning
on leaving anyone alive.

1187
01:29:37,327 --> 01:29:38,965
God.

1188
01:29:46,967 --> 01:29:48,525
- Hey.
BETH: Oh, my God. Come here.

1189
01:29:48,687 --> 01:29:49,676
- It's all right.
- Hey.

1190
01:29:49,847 --> 01:29:52,645
- He can't breathe.
- Sit down. I don't give a rat's ass.

1191
01:29:52,807 --> 01:29:56,083
- I'm sick of you people, man.
- Honey.

1192
01:29:56,527 --> 01:29:58,199
Vel.

1193
01:29:58,887 --> 01:30:01,037
Please help us.

1194
01:30:10,607 --> 01:30:12,677
We need to exchange you...

1195
01:30:12,847 --> 01:30:16,635
...for the money,
and then we'll let you go.

1196
01:30:17,847 --> 01:30:19,246
Okay?

1197
01:30:20,687 --> 01:30:22,484
You'll be all right.

1198
01:30:22,647 --> 01:30:23,875
Thank you.

1199
01:30:32,887 --> 01:30:34,161
They're slowing down.

1200
01:30:36,887 --> 01:30:38,639
Look.

1201
01:30:40,447 --> 01:30:41,880
[DOG WHIMPERING]

1202
01:30:45,647 --> 01:30:47,160
Rusty.

1203
01:30:47,767 --> 01:30:48,995
Rusty.

1204
01:30:49,167 --> 01:30:51,920
Come here, Rusty. It's okay.

1205
01:30:52,727 --> 01:30:54,957
Where are they, Rusty?

1206
01:30:56,007 --> 01:30:57,281
Where have they gone?

1207
01:30:57,447 --> 01:30:59,517
Where's Andy?

1208
01:31:03,887 --> 01:31:06,685
There's a house down there by the lake.
I see Beth's car.

1209
01:31:06,847 --> 01:31:08,326
- You got a cell phone?
- Yeah.

1210
01:31:08,487 --> 01:31:09,681
Call the police.

1211
01:31:09,847 --> 01:31:12,202
Shouldn't we just wait here
for the police?

1212
01:31:13,087 --> 01:31:14,645
No.

1213
01:31:14,807 --> 01:31:16,479
I can't. I can't wait.

1214
01:31:16,647 --> 01:31:18,046
Thanks for everything.

1215
01:31:18,207 --> 01:31:20,198
You got your job back.

1216
01:32:00,527 --> 01:32:02,165
Will he call?

1217
01:32:02,807 --> 01:32:05,002
You think he'll just give us the money,
no police?

1218
01:32:06,007 --> 01:32:08,919
He knows I'll kill his family
if he doesn't.

1219
01:32:11,927 --> 01:32:19,927
I just need to up the ante a little.

1220
01:32:19,927 --> 01:32:22,157
No. Please don't.
What are you doing?

1221
01:32:22,327 --> 01:32:24,079
- Let her go!
AND Y: No!

1222
01:32:24,247 --> 01:32:25,726
Stop it!

1223
01:32:26,527 --> 01:32:27,755
SARAH: My God!
BETH: Oh, my God!

1224
01:32:27,927 --> 01:32:29,246
